<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Clay</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-07-09"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 9, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Mr. Appleton’s despatch of May 22, (June
                            3,) No. 18, has been received.</p>
                        <p>It contains the orders in admiralty on the subject of the treatment of
                            American vessels during the present condition of our internal
                            affairs.</p>
                        <p>The subject seems to call for no special instruction to you, except to
                            express to the Russian government the satisfaction which this government
                            feels in regard to the conduct and friendly action of the Emperor.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Appleton is now with us, and we are deriving much profit from the
                            information he gives. We learn your high appreciation of his conduct in
                            his mission with pleasure.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius M. Clay</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>